The answer to your question is Tommy Johnson & Skip James. Look ‘em up, you’ll find plenty of supernatural references and occult suspicions. It was Son House who created the story about Robert selling his soul.

Supernatural took a few of Robert Johnson's images for their mythology.  It was said IRL that RJ did a deal with the devil at a crossroads to be the best blues singer ever and that when he died he was raving about hell hounds coming to get him.  The mythos of deals at a crossroads is pretty standard in majickal circles but it makes a good story.
